During this course, students will analyse and compose various types of texts. Students will learn about the most important models and techniques of practical text analysis and will further develop their written and oral communication skills. Authentic Norwegian / Swedish / Danish fiction, popular science, nonfiction and consumer-oriented texts, including culture-specific content, will be analysed. Course content varies from year to year according to the target audience: Swedish philologists work with Swedish, Danish philologists with Danish texts and Norwegian philologists with Norwegian texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to develop students' practical command of Norwegian / Danish / Swedish by working with various texts and introducing simple principles of composing and analysing different kinds of texts. By reading and analysing authentic texts, students will also get to know the characteristics of Norwegian / Swedish / Danish society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: - analyses different types of texts, applying the main models and techiques in text analysis; - recognises and identifies the most important characteristics of different types of texts and compares them (including fiction, popular science, nonfiction and consumer-oriented texts); - writes simple, typical texts in Norwegian / Swedish / Danish, applying the acquired knowledge; - has acquired basic knowledge about the Norwegian / Danish / Swedish society by working with authentic texts.
